Project Title
A concise description of what this project does and who it's for.

Description
This project implements a Node.js server with a focus on streaming and updating data. The server fetches and streams data, simulating a real-time data processing environment. It's designed to handle API updates and stream data to a client-side application, making it ideal for applications requiring real-time data updates such as dashboards, monitoring systems, or data analysis tools.

Features
Real-time data streaming using Node.js and Express.
Automatic data updates at regular intervals.
API endpoint to receive and update data.
In-memory data manipulation for simulating real-time data changes.
Logging and error handling for robust operation.
Prerequisites
Before you begin, ensure you have met the following requirements:

Node.js (version 21.5.0 or later)
Basic understanding of JavaScript and Node.js
An environment to run Node.js applications (like VS Code, Atom)
